                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200517-49-off291 t18200517-49-crimeloc293"></join>. On the 18th of April I saw the prisoner go into the building, and bring it out. I secured him with it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200517-49-person513">
                  JOSEPH 
                  CAPON
               <interp inst="t18200517-49-person513" type="surname" value="CAPON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200517-49-person513" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200517-49-person513" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am <rs id="t18200517-49-viclabel294" type="occupation">wharfinger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200517-49-victim511 t18200517-49-viclabel294"></join> to Mr. Smith; the block was on his premises. It is mine, and was used to hoist large stones on the building.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. It stood outside the building. A man unhooked it, and said it was very heavy. I lifted it to feel the weight, and this man seized me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200517-49-person514">
                  CHARLES 
                  HARWOOD
               <interp inst="t18200517-49-person514" type="surname" value="HARWOOD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200517-49-person514" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200517-49-person514" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             re-examined. I saw him go into the building without anything, and come out with the block. My fellow-workman called to him, but he went on with it. I secured him, and he said a man in the place lent it to him.</p>
